John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Clark","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which originated as an occupational name denoting a clerk (Latin <i>clericus</i>), in the Middle Ages a man in minor holy orders who earned his living by his ability to read and write. It is recorded as a given name in Britain from the late 17th century onwards. Since the 1930s, when it was associated particularly with the film star  Clark Gable  (  1901–60 ), it has been widely used as a given name, especially in North America."],"variants":[{"name":"Clarke","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which originated as an occupational name denoting a clerk (Latin <i>clericus</i>), in the Middle Ages a man in minor holy orders who earned his living by his ability to read and write. It is recorded as a given name in Britain from the late 17th century onwards. Since the 1930s, when it was associated particularly with the film star  Clark Gable  (  1901–60 ), it has been widely used as a given name, especially in North America."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":43,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":52,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":63,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Clark Webbe was born in 1506, in Sussex, England, his father, Robert de Arden, was 56 and his mother, Ann Harold, was 46. He had at least 3 daughters with Agnes Smythe. He died on 12 July 1571, in Barton Mills, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 65, and was buried in Great Sampford, Essex, England."},"et":{"1506–12 July 1571":"1506–12. juuli 1571","1506–1571":"1506–1571","1506–1572":"1506–1572","1538–1594":"1538–1594","1543–1594":"1543–1594","1560–Female":"1560–Surnud","1450–1517":"1450–1517","1460–1520":"1460–1520","19 MAY 1560":"19. mai 1560","12 July 1571":"12. juuli 1571","1594":"1594","1572":"1572","1450":"1450","1560":"1560","1571":"1571","1460":"1460","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1543":"1543","17 July 1571":"17. juuli 1571","1520":"1520","1506":"1506","1517":"1517","1538":"1538",", 1493":"1493","1549":"1549","Barton Mills, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Barton Mills, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Great Sampford, Essex, England":"Great Sampford, Essex, England","Barton Mills, Suffolk, England":"Barton Mills, Suffolk, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Chevington, Suffolk, England":"Chevington, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1506–12 July 1571":"1506–12. heinäkuuta 1571","1506–1571":"1506–15